The Golden Rule of Git
To avoid "Merge Conflicts" (where Git gets confused about which version is right), follow this daily habit:

Pull at the start of the day (git pull origin main).

Code and make your changes.

Push at the end of the day (git add, git commit, git push).

--------------------------------------------------
git pull origin main ===> pull code remote to local
git add README.md (README.md file should changed.)
git commit -m "Docs: Added Technologies Used section to README"
git push origin main